1.title: Where Three Have Gathered Together
1.plot: Frankie, Neffe, and Elite meet at Neffe's to see the new house, and do some family healing. But when you've been stuck in the mud, moving forward can be messy.

3.title: Episode #2.3
3.plot: Neffe has a business idea and Elite meets a music industry giant. Together, they learn some hard truths about Frankie.

4.title: Episode #2.4
4.plot: Neffe and Elite continue to develop their professional ventures, and Soullow wears yet another career hat.

5.title: Episode #2.5
5.plot: Elite confides a fear, while Neffe sees an idea become a reality. And speaking of reality, Soullow displays his inner TV producer.

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Neffe sets new rules with an old friend; Elite helps Kai step into his future.

1.title: Starting Over
1.plot: Frankie and Neffe are enjoying their new homes, but both still struggle with money. Without a job and the support of Keyshia, they are floundering financially, despite their newfound celebrity. Worried about the future, the two women meet with Manny to carve out a plan for their lives.

2.title: Baby Steps
2.plot: After Frankie and Neffe attend a joint session with the life coach, it's time for house calls. Lauren, the life coach, pays Frankie and Neffe visits at their homes to get a firsthand look at their lifestyles. The meetings provide a deeper glimpse into the issues that thwart each woman's growth.

3.title: Man Down
3.plot: In this episode, Neffe takes the advice of the life coach and attempts to build more trust with her mother, Frankie. She decides to let her children visit their grandmother for a weekend sleepover. Frankie is so excited about babysitting her grandkids, and the responsibility that it entails, that she goes on a shopping spree at the dollar store

4.title: Mother Knows Best
4.plot: Frankie gets upset with Neffe after she throws a birthday party for Soullow's son. Both women feel the other is taking the wrong approach to uniting their family.

5.title: Church Home
5.plot: Frankie & Neffe intimately profiles the entertaining mother and sister of R&B singer Keyshia Cole. The new reality series chronicles Frankie and Neffe as they strive to gain independence and maintain positive lifestyle changes.

6.title: The Christening
6.plot: Frankie & Neffe intimately profiles the entertaining mother and sister of R&B singer Keyshia Cole. The new reality series chronicles Frankie and Neffe as they strive to gain independence and maintain positive lifestyle changes.

7.title: D Day
7.plot: A conversation between Neffe and Elite about the joy of being reunited with their biological mom, Frankie, leads them on a quest to see if they have the same birth father. Because the two women look alike and have the same mother, Neffe believes her father, Ellis Vick Randolph, could be Elite's dad, too!

8.title: Lifting as We Climb
8.plot: In this episode, Neffe continues with the business of getting divorced from Clyde. She is upset to learn from her attorney that she is still married and must travel to California to see the divorce papers he filed. After the success of the christening, Frankie and Neffe are excited about the future and are determined to tackle more goals on the list they created with their life coach.

9.title: Celebration in Order
9.plot: Frankie, Neffe and Elite are back in Atlanta. Vick and Elite come to Neffe's house to hear the DNA test results. Frankie is at her home getting the test results. She refuses to go to Neffe's house because she disapproved of the test. During the reveal, we learn that Vick is Neffe's father, but not Elite's.

10.title: Reunited
10.plot: Neffe, Elite and Frankie are in Oakland trying to find Frankie's children. They go to Neffe's grandmother's house to get info on the kids, and while there they also speak on the phone with an adoption expert. The next day outside the courthouse, Neffe and Elite discover that it will take months to find their siblings.

-1.title: Give Me the Strength
-1.plot: Frankie drops a bomb, but Neffe and Elite refuse to blow up. Meanwhile, Neffe confronts her painful past, and Soullow's music career takes a turn.
